The seventh season of Big Brother Naija will stream in the United Kingdom. This feat will be happening following a statement from Adeola Oluwatobi, brand marketing, and partnerships manager at Showmax. For the second year in a row, Showmax will stream BBNaija to fans in sub-Saharan Africa and the United Kingdom.   I’ll not let you down, Adeleke tells Timi of Ede     Lagos steps down new abortion guidelines     Kuje attack: Senate shocked by no CCTV, porous security   “For the past two years, Showmax has been bringing BBNaija exclusives to viewers and fans. Last year we launched BBNaija S6: The Buzz, which became the go-to gist and opinion box for the reality series and we’re thrilled that it’s back for another season,” Oluwatobi said. Oluwatobi also confirmed the return of the highly entertaining BBNaija S7: The Buzz, which makes a comeback for a second season.